# Module Map

> Maps every domain/feature to concrete files in the codebase.
> Update whenever a new module is added or a major refactor happens.

---

## [Domain Name 1, e.g. Order Management]

| Layer | Path |
|-------|------|
| Controller | `app/Http/Controllers/OrderController.php` |
| Service | `app/Services/OrderService.php` |
| Repository | `app/Repositories/OrderRepository.php` |
| Model | `app/Models/Order.php`, `app/Models/OrderItem.php` |
| Events | `app/Events/OrderCreated.php` |
| Jobs | `app/Jobs/ProcessOrder.php` |
| Tests | `tests/Feature/OrderTest.php` |

**Domain rules:**
- [e.g. Status transitions MUST go through `OrderService::transition()` — never update status directly]
- [e.g. OrderItem cannot be deleted once the Order is `confirmed`]

---

## [Domain Name 2, e.g. Inventory]

| Layer | Path |
|-------|------|
| Controller | `app/Http/Controllers/InventoryController.php` |
| Service | `app/Services/InventoryService.php` |
| Model | `app/Models/Product.php`, `app/Models/Stock.php` |
| Tests | `tests/Feature/InventoryTest.php` |

**Domain rules:**
- [e.g. Negative stock is allowed for pre-order items]
- [e.g. All stock changes must go through `InventoryService::adjustStock()`]

---

## [Domain Name 3, e.g. Auth & User]

| Layer | Path |
|-------|------|
| Controller | `app/Http/Controllers/AuthController.php` |
| Middleware | `app/Http/Middleware/RoleMiddleware.php` |
| Model | `app/Models/User.php` |

**Available roles:** `admin`, `[role2]`, `[role3]`

**Domain rules:**
- [e.g. Use Gate/Policy for authorization — do not hardcode roles in controllers]

